    "comment": "Rationale: The creatine transporter transports creatine in a sodium-dependent manner (Fig.5).\n\nRat hippocampal neurons in culture are incubated with radiolabelled creatine for 15 min with or without sodium (Fig. 5a) indicating the requirements for sodium for the creatine transport into cells. The uptake of radiolabelled creatine is inhibited by creatine and creatine transporter competitive inhibitors (GPA, GBA, cycloCr, and GA, Fig. 5b).\n\nSamples of solubilized cells were taken for liquid scintillation counting protein determination.. Experimental description: Briefly, E18 embryos from time-mated Wistar rats were removed from the uterus...",
